3.1.1 COMPASS VMS HIGH LEVEL OVERVIEW Compass VMS is organized into a series of modules for cash center functions such as receiving incoming deposits, processing and balancing deposits, fulfilling outgoing orders, and controlling inventory. It also has features for cash center management such as order and deposit work assignment, configuration and administration, and reporting. The basic architecture of Compass VMS is as follows: • Windows-based Smart Client for teller operations in the Main Cash center • Windows-based Smart Client for teller operations in the Branches • Reporting functions are delivered via SAP Business Objects Enterprise • Java-based Web Client for management tasks • The clients communicate with the Middle Tier Java application which handles business logic and database access

Call and Notice About Call and Notice FusionCapital Opics Call and Notice is a complete and automated front to back-office STP, the Straight-Through Processing solution for increasing STP rates, reducing cost of transactions, and minimizing reconciliation. It facilitates performing various activities such as deal capturing, pricing, position management, profit/loss calculation, exception based workflow, payments, confirmations, accounting, and interfaces. The Call and Notice module maintains deposit and withdrawal activities to accounts that can be indexed to fixed, variable, tiered, or floating rates. Accounts can be maintained with or without a fixed maturity date and interest can be charged or paid to these accounts. Accruals are calculated daily and can be monitored by on-line inquiries, reports, and statements. The key features of FusionCapital Opics Call and Notice are: • On-line limits checks for customer exposure • On-line account balances and projections • Complete STP options including Standing Settlement Instructions (SSIs) • SWIFT payments, confirmations, and statements (MT 940, 941, 942 and 950) • Text customer statements • Tiered interest structure, rate re-fixing, overdraft, and sweep processing • Settlement to call and notice accounts from other product modules

Os serviços de submissão seguem uma interdependência lógica, sendo que só pode ser reportado os dados de actualização de um determinado cliente caso o mesmo já tenha sido reportado previamente. A infraestrutura interna está preparada para receber dados em paralelos (até 100 processos). Assim sendo, o Client REST pode submeter até 100 clientes ao mesmo tempo.

Os serviços de listagem e pesquisa apresentam no máximo 100 registos, que corresponde a uma página. Caso haja necessidade de listar a próxima página, deverá definir o parâmetro opcional página. Assim sendo, caso o parâmetro página lhe for definido o valor 1, o serviço irá retornar os primeiros 100 registos. Caso o valor for 2, o serviço irá retornar os próximos 100 registos e assim sucessivamente.

3.1.2.4 REPORT CLIENT (SAP BO LAUNCH PAD) Compass VMS provides the ability to generate reports from the Web Client; in addition with Business Objects it is possible for customers to directly build their own reports and call them from the Business Objects Launch Pad application. The Launch Pad is a thin client application; it is hosted on the Business Objects Report Server and is launched from any browser. For security reasons SSL should be enabled at the server to encrypt all messages to and from the Client.

3.1.2.3 WEB CLIENT The Compass VMS Web Client allows HQ internal users of Compass to administrate and configure the operations of the system. The Web Client is a thin client built using Java technologies; it is hosted on the WebSphere application server. The Client communicates directly with the Business layer. For security reasons SSL should be enabled at the server to encrypt all messages to and from the Client.
